messages.content: Please present the poem "静夜思" by Li Bai, including the original Chinese text and a reputable English translation, along with proper attribution to the author.

Here is the well-known poem "静夜思" (Quiet Night Thought) by the Tang dynasty poet Li Bai (李白):

Title: 静夜思 (Jìng Yè Sī) — Quiet Night Thought  
Author: 李白 (Li Bai), Tang Dynasty

Original Chinese text:  
床前明月光，  
疑是地上霜。  
举头望明月，  
低头思故乡。

English translation (by Witter Bynner):  
Before my bed, the bright moonlight,  
I suppose it is frost on the ground.  
I lift my head and watch the bright moon,  
I lower my head and think of home.

This poem expresses the poet’s feeling of homesickness while gazing at the moonlight on a quiet night. The imagery captures a simple yet profound moment of reflection and longing.

《静夜思》是唐代大诗人李白的诗作。此诗描写了旅居在外的抒情主人公秋日夜晚在屋内抬头望月而思念家乡的感受。前两句写主人公在作客他乡的特定环境中一刹那间所产生的错觉；后两句通过动作神态的刻画，深化主人公的思乡之情。全诗运用比喻、衬托等手法，表达客居思乡之情，语言清新朴素而韵味含蓄无穷，历来广为传诵。

message_buffer.content: Please present the poem "静夜思" by Li Bai, including the original Chinese text and a reputable English translation, along with proper attribution to the author.

Here is the well-known poem "静夜思" (Quiet Night Thought) by the Tang dynasty poet Li Bai (李白):

Title: 静夜思 (Jìng Yè Sī) — Quiet Night Thought  
Author: 李白 (Li Bai), Tang Dynasty

Original Chinese text:  
床前明月光，  
疑是地上霜。  
举头望明月，  
低头思故乡。

English translation (by Witter Bynner):  
Before my bed, the bright moonlight,  
I suppose it is frost on the ground.  
I lift my head and watch the bright moon,  
I lower my head and think of home.

This poem expresses the poet’s feeling of homesickness while gazing at the moonlight on a quiet night. The imagery captures a simple yet profound moment of reflection and longing.
